CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1953, pg. 12 reads: "Salvation Army March- Pictured with Chairman Eunice W. Cook are members of the committee of Pittsburghers who joined in Hill District March to bring in funds for the Salvation Army drive. The result exceeded expectations.  Left to right: Mmes. Bessie Keene, Irene Blanton, Lacy Tabb, Ealie Greenlee, Hattie Southers, Miss Joan Tucker, Mmes. Marguerite Smart, Lucille Hayes, Eunice W. Cook, Lillian Donald, Thelma Snead. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of eleven women, standing left to right; Bessie Keene, Irene Blanton, Lacy Tabb, Ealie Greenlee, Hattie Southers, Joan Tucker, and Marguerite Smart, seated; Lucille Hayes, Eunice W. Cook, Lillian Donald, and Thelma Snead, gathered around table with donation cans for Salvation Army
